label.value: denial belief about a responsibility to act

definition.value: A <denial belief> that holds that the person has no responsibility to act to address a problem.
A <denial belief> that holds that a norm is not relevant in a given scenario.
A <desired standard> for a self-regulatory process that the person wishes to enact.
A <desired standard> for a self-identity that the person wishes to attain.

label.value: efficacy belief for a behaviour and its associated outcomes

definition.value: A <belief> about some person’s capability to organise and execute a behaviour and achieve the outcomes associated with this behaviour.
A <mental process> in which a person experiences another person’s perspective, thoughts and feelings.
A <subjective feeling> of not knowing something.

label.value: feeling of uncertainty about one’s behaviour

definition.value: A <feeling of uncertainty> about the best course of action.
A <bodily process> that reduces negative affect resulting from goal conflict.

This class refers to any behaviour, cognitive or emotional process that has the function of reducing goal conflict, including changing goals, and cognitive restructuring to make goals seem compatible.
A <social group process> that results in development of some group identity.
A <mental capability> to form a cognitive representation of something that has not been directly experienced.
A <bodily disposition> that is either capability or motivation.

label.value: low mental capability to enact a behaviour

definition.value: <Low capability to enact a behaviour> that involves mental processes.
A <perceived descriptive behavioural norm> in which the prevalence of a behaviour is overestimated.
This is the belief of an individual.
A <goal pursuit process> that is maintained despite barriers.

label.value: positive evaluative belief about achieving a goal

definition.value: An <evaluative belief about achieving a goal> in which the goal attainment is evaluated positively.

label.value: positive evaluative belief about interacting with others

definition.value: A <positive evaluative belief about a behaviour> that involves interacting with other people.

label.value: self-awareness process in relation to a problem

definition.value: A <mental process> that increases the accuracy of one’s cognitive representation of oneself through engaging with a problem.

label.value: self-identity appraisal informed by one’s behaviour

definition.value: A <self-identity appraisal process> that is informed by the person’s behaviour.
An <emotional-relevance appraisal process> that results in some appraisal of oneself.
<Pleasure> derived from receiving social approval
<Mental categorising> where what is being categorised are parts of the social environmental system.
<Pleasure> derived from feeling emotionally connected to others.

label.value: social consequence of behaviour appraisal process

definition.value: A <behavioural consequences appraisal process> in which the consequence concerns the social environmental system.
A <interpersonal process> that has some social group as a participant.
<Pleasure> derived from social interaction.

label.value: strength of group support for an intervention

definition.value: A <social group attribute> that is the extent to which its members positively evaluate an intervention.
A <bodily disposition> that is the aggregate of internal influences on behaviour.
A <perceived descriptive behavioural norm> in which the prevalence of a behaviour is underestimated.
This is the belief of an individual.
A personal attribute that is the extent to which the person’s past behaviour has reached or exceeded a standard.
A social role in which the holder is given or creates authority to exert influence on other members of a social group.
There are many usages of the term ‘leadership'. This class refers to one particular usage.
A social group that is part of a person’s social environmental system and with which the person does not identify.

label.value: person in a social environmental system

definition.value: A <person> who is part of a social environmental system.
A <disposition> that decreases the likelihood of engaging with harmful behaviour.
A social grouping that identifies as such and sometimes acts collectively.
A human population who share some common attribute that involves some form of social interaction.
Population can be two or more people. the interaction may involve how other people treat members of the group.
A <personal attribute> that, together with other attributes, characterises a person’s position in society.
This can include social history, current circumstances, age, gender identity, occupation, education level, socio-economic position (status or group), ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability

label.value: evaluative belief about achieving a goal

definition.value: An <evaluative belief> about acting in a way that achieves a goal.
A <belief> about one's capabilities to organise and execute a process or achieve an outcome.
A social behavioural consequence of some family member.
A behavioural consequence of a member of the person’s social environmental system.
A social behavioural consequence that is beyond the person’s family.
A behavioural attribute that is the level of convenience, ease or comfort of a behaviour.
A <social environmental disposition> that is realised as being safe from harm.
An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.
An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.
A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

value.value: b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])

definition.value: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.

value.value: p is a process = Def. p is an occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [083-003])
